# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

New API is an LLM gateway and AI asset management system built on [One API](https://github.com/songquanpeng/one-api). It provides a unified API interface for multiple AI providers with billing, user management, and channel routing capabilities.

## Build & Run Commands

### Backend (Go)
```bash
# Run development server
go run main.go

# Build binary
go build -o new-api main.go
```

### Frontend (React + Vite)
```bash
cd web
bun install
bun run dev      # Development server
bun run build    # Production build
bun run lint     # Check formatting (prettier)
bun run lint:fix # Fix formatting
```

### Full Build (Makefile)
```bash
make all              # Build frontend + start backend
make build-frontend   # Build frontend only
make start-backend    # Start backend only
```

### Docker
```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

## Architecture

### Backend Structure

- `main.go` - Application entry point, initializes resources, sets up Gin server with embedded frontend
- `router/` - HTTP route definitions
  - `api-router.go` - Management API routes (users, channels, tokens, etc.)
  - `relay-router.go` - AI API relay routes (OpenAI, Claude, Gemini compatible endpoints)
- `controller/` - HTTP handlers for management APIs
- `relay/` - AI request relay logic
  - `channel/` - Provider-specific adapters (openai, claude, gemini, aws, azure, etc.)
  - `*_handler.go` - Request handlers for different API formats
- `middleware/` - Gin middleware (auth, rate limiting, distributor for channel selection)
- `model/` - Database models and business logic (GORM)
- `service/` - Shared services (HTTP client, token encoders)
- `dto/` - Data transfer objects for API requests/responses
- `constant/` - Application constants and enums
- `common/` - Utilities (crypto, database, redis, validation)
- `setting/` - Configuration and ratio settings

### Frontend Structure (web/)

React 18 + Vite application using:
- Semi Design UI components (@douyinfe/semi-ui)
- React Router for navigation
- i18next for internationalization (zh, en, fr, ja)
- VChart for data visualization

### Key Patterns

**Channel Adapters**: Each AI provider has an adapter in `relay/channel/` implementing a common interface. The `middleware/distributor.go` selects appropriate channels based on model, user group, and availability.

**Relay Flow**: Request → TokenAuth → ModelRateLimit → Distribute (channel selection) → Provider Adapter → Response

**Database**: Supports SQLite (default), MySQL, PostgreSQL via GORM. Log database can be separate (`LOG_SQL_DSN`).

**Caching**: Redis optional (`REDIS_CONN_STRING`), falls back to memory cache (`MEMORY_CACHE_ENABLED`).

## Environment Configuration

Copy `.env.example` to `.env`. Key variables:
- `PORT` - Server port (default 3000)
- `SQL_DSN` - Database connection string
- `REDIS_CONN_STRING` - Redis connection
- `SESSION_SECRET` - Required for multi-node deployment
- `CRYPTO_SECRET` - Required when using Redis

## Supported AI Providers

Channel adapters exist for: OpenAI, Azure, Claude/Anthropic, AWS Bedrock, Google Gemini/Vertex, Cohere, Coze, DeepSeek, Ollama, Mistral, xAI, Cloudflare, and many Chinese providers (Ali, Baidu, Tencent, Zhipu, etc.)
